response.overview: Fresh from supporting Michael McIntyre and Romesh Ranganathan, 'Fringe favourite' (BroadwayWorld.com) Jake Lambert returns with another 'highly entertaining hour' (One4Review.co.uk) full of 'subtlety and wit throughout' (LondonTheatre1.com), and 'brilliant one-liners' (Chortle.co.uk). Jake 'catalyses laughter that cannot be contained' (EdFestMag.com). As seen on Comedy Central and BBC Two. Writer for Mock The Week, The Ranganation, The Apprentice: You're Fired, 8 Out Of 10 Cats and The News Quiz. This is sure to be another 'solidly entertaining' (Scotsman) hour that proves why he 'could easily be a TV star' (BeyondTheJoke.co.uk).
response.title: Jake Lambert: Liminal
